Make sure your diet is primarily made up of protein. If you're serious about your training, aim for a gram of protein per pound of your weight.

Mistake #3: Focusing on cardio instead of weight lifting. Lifting weights is key to building shape and toning your body. Weight training is also crucial for reducing body fat, as it helps to increase muscle mass, which in turn burns more calories even at rest.
